JOHANNESBURG - A Pretoria high court judge has declared invalid the government's decision to withdraw from the International Criminal Court.JUST IN: The DA has won its court bid to declare SA governments decision to withdraw from #ICC as invalid & unconstitutional.The court ordered that the decision be revoked.Justice Minister Michael Masutha announced that the country had initiated the process of withdrawing from the ICC last year, citing bias against African nations.The move followed South Africa s failure to arrest Sudanese President Omar al-Bashir when he visited the country last year. The Sudanese leader is wanted by the ICC for crimes against humanity allegedly committed in his country.The DA took the decision to court, saying Parliament had not been consulted, as required by the Constitution.The DA reaction to #ICC court ruling. pic.twitter.com/aUPLmT3DeSeNCA